This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama in November 2014. The memorandum addresses the need to modernize and streamline the U.S. immigrant visa system for the 21st century. It highlights the contributions of immigrants to the U.S. economy and emphasizes the importance of immigration reform for economic growth, national security, and moral reasons. The memorandum directs the Secretaries of State and Homeland Security to develop recommendations, in consultation with various stakeholders, to improve the legal immigration system, including visa processing, reducing government costs, improving services for applicants, and combating waste, fraud, and abuse. It also calls for recommendations to ensure that administrative policies use all available immigrant visa numbers and for modernizing the information technology infrastructure underlying the visa processing system. The memorandum concludes with general provisions, stating that it does not impair existing authorities or create any rights or benefits enforceable by any party.